Pre-heat your #oven to 180 degrees. Now get all your vegetables prepped and ready for action! Peel and chop your @carrot{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces about 1/2cm) and @onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped into small pieces about 1/2cm), and set aside. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1}(cored and sliced into strips) and slice it into strips. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and finely chop up the @coriander{3}(finely chopped).

> To see how to dice an onion check out our Youtube Channel by searching HelloFreshUK.

Time to make the Chermoula! Put the chopped coriander in a #bowl with the @ras-el-Hanout{1/2%tsp}, garlic and grate the zest of @lemon{1/2}(zested) into the bowl. Add the juice of @lemon{1/2}(juiced) and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Give it a good stir and then add the @British chicken thighs{4} to the bowl.

Mix it around either with your hands or a #spoon, making sure the chicken gets a good coating of the chermoula. Season with some @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and pop onto a #baking tray{}. Put the chicken on the top shelf of the #oven for ~{25%minutes} until it is cooked and no longer pink inside.

Mix the peppers with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, put them on a #baking tray{} and into the #oven to roast. They should be done in ~{20%minutes}.

Put a #frying pan{} on a medium heat with @oil{1%tsp} and then add the @diced chorizo{1}. Cook for about ~{5%minutes} until the chorizo is a little crispy and has released some of its oils. Take the chorizo out of the pan and set aside.

> When you take the chorizo out of the pan try to leave the oil in so the vegetables pick up some lovely chorizo-ey flavour. If the pan doesn't have much oil left in it, add @?oil{1%tbsp}, then add the onion and carrot to the pan. Cook for about 5 mins or until the vegetables are soft.

Drain the @organic lentils{1}(drained) in a #sieve and run some water through them to rinse them. Add the chorizo back into the pan with the vegetables along with the lentils. Cook for about ~{4%minutes}, stirring to make sure everything is combined. Take off the heat.

When the chicken and peppers are ready, serve the chicken on top of the lentils with the peppers on the side. Enjoy!